HED-BERT Anonymous Review Release — License Notice

This source release is provided for the sole purpose of NeurIPS 2026
double-blind peer review and follow-on reproducibility evaluation.

The released source code is intended to be used together with the
following public, non-derivative-restricted EEG corpora:

  - HBN-EEG (Healthy Brain Network EEG), OpenNeuro datasets
    ds005505 through ds005516 (releases 1 through 11).
    Distributed under the Healthy Brain Network research-only data
    use agreement; see https://openneuro.org for terms.
  - ERP-CORE, NEMAR dataset nm000132. Distributed under CC-BY 4.0;
    see https://nemar.org for terms.

By using this code, you agree to:

  1. Respect the license and data-use terms of HBN-EEG and ERP-CORE
     listed above. Do not redistribute the underlying recordings.
  2. Use this artifact for research purposes only during the review
     window. Camera-ready will replace this anonymous distribution
     with a permissively licensed public repository.
  3. Not apply pretrained checkpoints to EEG recordings collected
     without informed consent. See MODEL_CARD.md for the full misuse
     statement.

The code itself, exclusive of any bundled checkpoints, is provided
as-is, without warranty of any kind. Pretrained weights inherit the
source-corpus license restrictions of HBN-EEG and ERP-CORE.

For the full intended-use, scope, and misuse statement, see
MODEL_CARD.md.
